title: DE-1 Plasma Wave Instrument (PWI) Low Frequency Correlator (LFC) Electric and Magnetic Field Spectral Density - Donald Gurnett (University Iowa)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/de/de1/waves_pwi/lfc-spectra_cdaweb/1981/de1_pwi_lfc-spectra_19810916_v01.cdf. The most common cadence occurred for 95.4545% of the 1008 timesteps. Cadence = 32000000000 [ns] = PT32S.

parameters.name: Time
parameters.x_description: Event time for the start of the sweep

parameters.name: Ex_Spectra_Reorder
parameters.description: Spin Plane E-Field (LFC Ex) Spectra, 200 meter antenna, 104 Hz to 409 kHz [data monotonically sorted based on dependencies]. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function reorder_data (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['Ex_Spectra', 'Frequencies']. Note that some COMPONENTS may not be available from the HAPI interface. They are accessible from the raw CDF files, however.
